  <div class="panel">
    <p class="faq-q-bold">Q: What is the difference between the Integrated, Removable Cover & Cooling Blankets?</p>  
    <p class="faq-a-normal">A: The difference between the types of Luxome blankets is simple: One has a removable premium cover and the other has the premium cover sewn directly onto the blanket (Integrated) and is not removable.</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">Our Cooling Weighted Blankets are simply a selection of our coolest Integrated Cover and Removable Cover blankets.  The cooling aspect is due to the bamboo lyocell fabric we use, as lyocell from bamboo is a natural temperature regulating fabric.</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">We also answer “What are the blankets made of?” below.</p>
    
    <p class="faq-q-bold">Q: Which size/weight is right for me?</p>  
    <p class="faq-a-normal">A: For children (4+) we recommend the small size (42"x56" - 8lbs). For adolescents, smaller adults, and couch throws we recommend the medium size (54"x72" - 15lbs). For most adults we recommend the large size (60"x80" - 18lbs). For a sharable blanket, we recommend the extra large (100"x85" – 30lbs.) </p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">Selecting a weight based on body weight actually has no scientific basis and the weight per square foot can vary greatly depending on the blanket size. All of our blankets are specifically optimized to a perfect weight per square foot based on extensive user testing that included, men, women, adolescents, and children of all shapes and sizes. So, just select a size and rest assured it's the right weight.</p>
    
    <p class="faq-q-bold">Q: What are your blankets made of?</p>  
    <p class="faq-a-normal">A: For our Removable Cover Weighted Blankets, the inner blanket has an outer shell of 100% cotton with a thread count of 233. This higher thread count is to ensure the fabric density required to hold in the 1mm glass beads throughout use and washing. The higher thread count is also useful to use the blanket without a cover to provide additional softness. </p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">Underneath the outer cotton shell are 1mm natural, 100% lead-free, hypoallergenic, glass beads sewn into small square pockets for even weight distribution. They are not sharp and do not cause any damage to the blanket. With the glass beads is polyester fabric filling to limit the beads from moving around within their section. </p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">The integrated blankets are the exact same, but underneath the integrated cover sewn into the blanket is a layer of polyester to provide additional strength and durability for washing.</p>
    
    <p class="faq-q-bold">Q: What is the difference between Bamboo Lyocell & Minky?</p>  
    <p class="faq-a-normal">A: Lyocell from bamboo is soft, cool and silky to the touch. It is a naturally thermal-regulating and moisture-wicking fabric, that is also hypoallergenic and antibacterial. This is a favorite among those that tend to regularly sleep hot. </p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">Minky is soft and velvety to the touch. It is similar to fleece and microfiber, so it will retain heat for a warmer experience. </p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">Our Bamboo Lyocell + Minky cover options provides a cool, bamboo lyocell side and cozy, Minky side all in one flippable cover to provide the best of both worlds. </p>
    
    <p class="faq-q-bold">Q: Are your blankets machine washable?</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">A: YES! While a lot of other companies require their blankets to be hand washed only, ALL types of Luxome weighted blankets, up to 18lbs, can be machine washed and dried. Because we use higher quality fabrics with higher thread counts, our blankets can be machine washed & dried without any problems.</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">If you want to learn more about why our blankets are the best, we deconstruct the weighted blanket in some of our <a href="https://luxome.com/pages/videos" class="a-link-faq">VIDEOS</a>.</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">We also posted detailed <a class="faq__link" href="https://luxome.com/pages/care-instructions" class="a-link-faq">CARE INSTRUCTIONS</a> for all Luxome blankets. </p>
    
    <p class="faq-q-bold">Q: Will the blanket cover my bed?</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">A: Weighted blankets have been studied and designed to be used individually. We optimize ours to a specific weight per square foot for the best experience and matched our sizes to bed sizes so they can look great while you’re not using them. However, they are not the same dimensions as standard blankets that drape over the bed since that would require a lot of wasted weight in order to maintain our ideal weight per square foot.</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">View our comprehensive <a href="#" id="size-guide-modal-link-faq" class="a-link-faq">SIZE GUIDE</a> here</p>
    {%- include 'modal-size-guide', modalId: "size-guide-modal-link-faq" -%}
    
    <p class="faq-q-bold">Q: Is your blanket really cooling?</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">A: We designed our weighted blankets to minimize excess heat, but unfortunately we can't eliminate it. The main function of a blanket is to provide warmth, so we did our best to minimize that warmth while providing additional weight. </p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">Our weighted blankets are much cooler than competitive blankets since we use breathable, high-quality materials and avoid several layers of cheap polyester or cotton. When you combine our breathable core construction with outer fabrics like our 300TC Bamboo Lyocell, our weighted blankets are as cool as you can make a weighted blanket. However, they are still blankets and will still provide warmth, just a lot less warmth than a comparable blanket. </p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">If you are looking for our coolest blankets, we’d recommend the following, in order:</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">
      Bamboo Lyocell Integrated Blanket<br />
      Bamboo Lyocell Removable Cover Blanket<br />
      Bamboo Lyocell + Minky Integrated Blanket<br />
      Bamboo Lyocell + Minky Removable Cover Blanket
    </p>
    
    <p class="faq-q-bold">Q: Where is my removable cover?</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">A: To save you unnecessary time and hassle, your removable cover weighted blanket arrives with the removable cover already attached. Since we did such a great job hiding the zipper, it may be hard to locate Simply find the black LUXOME tag, then slowly follow the seam towards the center and you’ll find the zipper in between the black Luxome tag and the middle of the blanket. </p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">View our video on blanket covers here: <a href="https://luxome.com/blogs/videos/blanket-covers">https://luxome.com/blogs/videos/blanket-covers</a></p>

    <p class="faq-q-bold">Q: How do I remove/reattach the removable cover?</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">A: To remove your Removable Cover, simply open the zipper (located along the same side as the black Luxome tag), turn the cover inside out and untie each connection.  To reattach, lay the weighted insert flat, lay the cover inside out on the insert, and retie each connection.  Then, carefully, turn the cover & insert right side out by either feeding your arms through the cover opening to the far corners of the blanket, or by using a roll method. </p>
    
    <p class="faq-q-bold">Q: Can I add a removable cover to my Integrated Cover blanket?</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">A: Our Integrated Cover blankets are designed to be used without a cover, which is why we made them machine washable and removed the loops. If you are specifically looking for a blanket with a removable cover, check out our Removable Cover Weighted Blankets.</p>
    
    <p class="faq-q-bold">Q: Does the Integrated Cover blanket come in the XL 30lb size?</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">A: Since we do not consider our XL 30lb blanket to be machine washable, this size is only available with a removable cover for easy care and maintenance. </p>
    
    <p class="faq-q-bold">Q: What if my blanket is too heavy?</p>
    <p class="faq-a-normal">A: While we would love to be able to guarantee that everyone will experience the weighted blanket in the same way, how a person reacts to the additional weight varies. Some people will feel its benefits right away, and some may need up to 7-10 nights for their body to adjust to the additional weight. For others, it just may not work out at all. Trying the blanket for multiple nights is the best way to know if your body will adjust to the additional weight and why we offer a 30-day return policy.</p>
